  <section>
    <h2>Selectable rows</h2>
    <p>Put a <code>.form-check-input</code> in the first column to let people pick rows. The header checkbox is the bulk toggle; flip <code>.table-active</code> on the row to show the selected state. On this demo page, <code>data-demo-select-rows</code> wires it up live — try clicking the checkboxes.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <table class="table table-hover align-middle" data-demo-select-rows>
      <thead class="table-header-alt">
        <tr>
          <th scope="col" style="width: 1rem;">
            <input class="form-check-input m-0" type="checkbox" aria-label="Select all subscribers" />
          </th>
          <th scope="col">Email</th>
          <th scope="col">Source</th>
          <th scope="col">Subscribed</th>
          <th scope="col">Status</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><input class="form-check-input m-0" type="checkbox" aria-label="Select maya@acme.co" /></td>
          <td>maya@acme.co</td>
          <td>Landing page</td>
          <td>Jun 02</td>
          <td><span class="badge badge-light-success">Confirmed</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="table-active">
          <td><input class="form-check-input m-0" type="checkbox" aria-label="Select mateo@acme.co" checked /></td>
